<h1>Ajay Rajani</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://www.ajayrajani.com/now">ajayrajani.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
New York
NY
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Investor (in startups like Grovo, Inventure, Compology, OkHi, Knewton)  & entrepreneur (Formerly: Founding CMO @ Inventure <<a href="http://inventure.com>,">http://inventure.com>,</a> Head of Product @ Grovo <<a href="http://www.grovo.com>.">http://www.grovo.com>.</a> Currently: testing Haiku <<a href="http://myhaiku.co>">http://myhaiku.co></a> & some other ideas)
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I'm an aspiring merchant of progress.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I love building things that push the world forward, and working with the people behind them.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
I'm a wildly curious and easily inspired person, but building stuff is hard. I always test manually before engineering/automating. And everything takes more work than expected, so I try not to waste energy on stuff that doesn't have the potential for major & systemic impact.  My motto is: "Empathize -> Hypothesize -> Test -> Scale"
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
Anything Chamath <<a href="https://twitter.com/chamath>">https://twitter.com/chamath></a> says.
</p>

